{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/CustomStateAndTraits","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Custom State and Traits","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Global","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GlobalValue","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/StateValue"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Custom-State-and-Traits"}],"kind":"article","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"metadata":{"title":"Custom State and Traits","modules":[{"name":"Gnusto"}],"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gnusto\/customstateandtraits"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Carry your own data on entities and in globals, alongside the engine’s closed core."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Global"},{"type":"text","text":" normally holds one scalar ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Bool"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Int"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Double"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"String"},{"type":"text","text":"), and an item or location carries only the traits the engine knows about ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"wearable"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"surface"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dark"},{"type":"text","text":", …). Those closed sets are deliberate: the engine’s behavior branches over a small, readable vocabulary you can audit at a glance. But a game system — a wallet, combat stats, an item’s price — needs to carry data the engine itself never acts on. Custom state and custom traits are the open edges beside that closed core: unlimited declarative data for your rules to read and write, boxed through the same storage the engine already saves and restores."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The split is the whole idea. "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The engine still switches only on the closed core."}]},{"type":"text","text":" Your custom values ride along type-erased and are only ever read by your own rule code."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","text":"Rich `@Global` state","anchor":"Rich-Global-state","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Any "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Codable & Sendable"},{"type":"text","text":" type can be a global. Conform it to "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GlobalValue"},{"type":"text","text":" with an empty conformance — the default implementation JSON-boxes it into the type-erased "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/StateValue\/data(typeName:bytes:)"},{"type":"text","text":" case, so there’s nothing to hand-pack:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["struct Purse: Codable, Sendable, GlobalValue {","    var coins: Int","    var receipts: [String] = []","}","","struct MyGame: Game {","    @Global var purse = Purse(coins: 10)","    \/\/ …","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Read and write it in rules exactly like a scalar global — it participates in the turn’s commit and in save\/restore through the one world-state funnel:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["lantern.before(Intent(\"buy\")) {","    guard purse.coins >= 5 else { try refuse(\"You can't afford it.\") }","    purse.coins -= 5","    try reply(\"Sold. You have \\(purse.coins) coins left.\")","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The type needs only "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Codable"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Sendable"},{"type":"text","text":" — not "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Hashable"},{"type":"text","text":". The boxed bytes are what participate in the world state’s equality and hashing."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"note","type":"aside","name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A custom global is stored as opaque bytes, so if you change its shape, an old save may no longer decode — the global then falls back to its declared default. Keep plugin\/system state structs additive and optional-tolerant (new fields with defaults), and you’ll stay compatible. Versioned codecs are a later effort."}]}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Custom traits","anchor":"Custom-traits","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Declare a custom property inside an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Item { … }"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Location { … }"},{"type":"text","text":" block with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"trait(_:_:)"},{"type":"text","text":". The value is boxed with the same rule as a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Global"},{"type":"text","text":", so a scalar or a whole struct both work:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let lantern = Item {","    name(\"brass lantern\")","    trait(\"price\", 5)","}","","let docks = Location {","    name(\"The Docks\")","    trait(\"region\", \"waterfront\")","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Read it back on the live proxy with the typed accessor, which returns "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" when the trait is absent or stored as a different type:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let price = lantern.trait(\"price\", as: Int.self) ?? 0"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Custom traits are "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"immutable declared facts"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — they never touch the world state. For per-entity state that "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"changes"}]},{"type":"text","text":" during play (an item’s current charge, a creature’s HP), use a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Global"},{"type":"text","text":" keyed however your system needs; traits are for the fixed properties an entity is born with."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","text":"Closed core, open edges","anchor":"Closed-core-open-edges","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The engine never switches on a custom trait or a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".data"},{"type":"text","text":" global — it only branches over the closed "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/ItemTrait"},{"type":"text","text":"\/"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/LocationTrait"},{"type":"text","text":" kinds and scalar "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/StateValue"},{"type":"text","text":" cases it acts on ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isSurface"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isWearable"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dark"},{"type":"text","text":", …). That’s what keeps the engine auditable: every behavior it drives is still visible in a handful of small enums, while your systems get unlimited declarative properties that only your rules interpret."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","text":"Worked example","anchor":"Worked-example","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Tests\/GnustoTests\/Support\/CustomStateGames.swift"},{"type":"text","text":" builds "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ShopGame"},{"type":"text","text":": a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Purse"},{"type":"text","text":" struct held in a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Global"},{"type":"text","text":", a lantern with a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"trait(\"price\", 5)"},{"type":"text","text":", and a game-defined "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"buy"},{"type":"text","text":" verb whose rule reads the price and debits the purse — the commerce plugin in miniature. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CustomStateTests"},{"type":"text","text":" boots it and confirms the struct global round-trips through save\/restore, the custom trait reads back through the typed accessor, and absent\/wrong-type reads return "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","text":"See also","anchor":"See-also","level":2},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/WritingRules","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Plugins","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Global","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GlobalValue","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}]}]}]}]}],"references":{"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A Swift engine for writing parser-driven interactive fiction — text adventures in the tradition of Zork and Infocom’s ZIL."}],"title":"Gnusto"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/LocationTrait":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/LocationTrait","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"LocationTrait","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"LocationTrait"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A single fact about a location, stated inside a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Location { … }"},{"type":"text","text":" block."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/locationtrait","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"LocationTrait","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/StateValue":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/StateValue","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/statevalue","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"StateValue"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"StateValue"}],"title":"StateValue","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A value that can live in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"WorldState"},{"type":"text","text":"’s global storage. The scalar cases"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"each pair with a dedicated "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GlobalValue"},{"type":"text","text":" conformance; "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/StateValue\/data(typeName:bytes:)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is the type-erased case that carries any other "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Codable"},{"text":" value, so custom","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"state structs and custom traits need no new case of their own."}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/StateValue/data(typeName:bytes:)":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/StateValue\/data(typeName:bytes:)","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/statevalue\/data(typename:bytes:)","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"case","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"data","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"typeName","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"String","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"bytes","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Data","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:10Foundation4DataV"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"title":"StateValue.data(typeName:bytes:)","abstract":[]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/WritingRules":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/WritingRules","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/writingrules","kind":"article","role":"article","title":"Writing Rules","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Attach game logic to items, locations, and the world."}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Global":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Global","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"Global","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Global"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Custom game state with the same ergonomics as built-in state:"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/global","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Global"}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Plugins":{"role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Plugins","type":"topic","kind":"article","title":"Plugins","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Package a reusable game system as an importable unit of verbs and rules."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/plugins"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/ItemTrait":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/ItemTrait","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/itemtrait","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ItemTrait"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"ItemTrait"}],"title":"ItemTrait","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A single fact about an item, stated inside an "},{"code":"Item { … }","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" block."}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/GlobalValue":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GlobalValue","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/globalvalue","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GlobalValue","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"GlobalValue","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"GlobalValue","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Types usable with the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Global"},{"type":"text","text":" property wrapper."}]}}}